question: Show all names of institutions from France except institutions from the territorial region of Paris
sql_query: select i.institutions_name from institutions as i join countries as c on c.unics_id = i.country_id where country_name = 'France' except select i.institutions_name from institutions as i join countries as c on c.unics_id = i.country_id join eu_territorial_units as etu on i.geocode_regions_3 = etu.geocode_regions where country_name = 'France' and etu.description = 'Paris'
sparql_query: SELECT distinct?col1 WHERE { { SELECT (?T1_institutions_name as ?col1) WHERE { ?T1 a dbo:institutions . ?T2 a dbo:countries . ?T1 dbo:country_id ?T2 . ?T1 dbo:institutions_name ?T1_institutions_name . ?T2 dbo:country_name ?T2_country_name . FILTER(?T2_country_name = 'France') . }} MINUS {SELECT (?T3_institutions_name as ?col1) WHERE { ?T3 a dbo:institutions . ?T4 a dbo:countries . ?T3 dbo:country_id ?T4 . ?T3 dbo:institutions_name ?T3_institutions_name . ?T4 dbo:country_name ?T4_country_name . ?T5 dbo:description ?T5_description . ?T5 a dbo:eu_territorial_units . ?T3 dbo:geocode_regions_3 ?T5 . ?T3 dbo:institutions_name ?T3_institutions_name . ?T4 dbo:country_name ?T4_country_name . ?T5 dbo:description ?T5_description . FILTER(?T4_country_name = 'France' && ?T5_description = 'Paris') . } } }

question: Show the number of projects by program of the Ile-de-France region
sql_query: select t4.title, count(distinct t2.project) from projects as t1 join project_members as t2 on t2.project=t1.unics_id join project_programmes as t3 on t3.project=t2.project join programmes as t4 on t4.code=t3.programme where t2.region_name='Ile-de-France' group by t4.title

question: Show the institutions from the region with code ES51 that participate in H2020 projects
sql_query: select distinct t1.institutions_name from institutions as t1 join project_members as t2 on t2.institution_id=t1.unics_id join projects as t3 on t3.unics_id=t2.project where t2.region_code='ES51' and t3.framework_program='H2020'

question: Show all the information of the projects of the region of Z端rich that started after 2014
sql_query: select distinct t1.* from projects as t1 join project_members as t2 on t2.project=t1.unics_id where t2.region_name='Z端rich' and t1.start_year > 2014

question: Show the number of H2020 projects by year of the region of Z端rich
sql_query: select t1.start_year, count(distinct t1.unics_id) from projects as t1 join project_members as t2 on t2.project=t1.unics_id where t2.region_name='Z端rich' and t1.framework_program='H2020' group by t1.start_year

question: Show the number of H2020 projects and funding received by the region with code CH04 each year
sql_query: select t1.start_year, count(distinct t1.unics_id), sum(t2.ec_contribution) from projects as t1 join project_members as t2 on t2.project=t1.unics_id where t2.region_code='CH04' and t1.framework_program='H2020' group by t1.start_year

question: Show the funding by program of the region with code EL30
sql_query: select t2.title, sum(t3.ec_contribution) from project_programmes as t1 join programmes as t2 on t2.code=t1.programme join project_members as t3 on t3.project=t1.project where t3.region_code='EL30' group by t2.title

question: Show the funding by topic of the H2020 projects of the region with code EL30
sql_query: select t2.title, sum(t3.ec_contribution) from project_topics as t1 join topics as t2 on t2.code=t1.topic join project_members as t3 on t3.project=t1.project join projects as t4 on t4.unics_id=t1.project where t3.region_code='EL30' and t4.framework_program='H2020' group by t2.title

question: Show the number of H2020 projects of the Dresden region grouped by program
sql_query: select t2.title, count(distinct t1.project) from project_programmes as t1 join programmes as t2 on t2.code=t1.programme join project_members as t3 on t3.project=t1.project where t3.region_name='Dresden' group by t2.title

question: Rank the institutions from the Dresden region by the H2020 funding received
sql_query: select t3.institutions_name, sum(t1.ec_contribution) from project_members as t1 join projects as t2 on t2.unics_id=t1.project join institutions as t3 on t3.unics_id=t1.institution_id where t1.region_name='Dresden' and t2.framework_program='H2020' group by t3.institutions_name order by sum(t1.ec_contribution) desc

question: Rank the institutions from the Dresden region by H2020 funding and number of projects
sql_query: select t3.institutions_name, sum(t1.ec_contribution), count(distinct t1.project) from project_members as t1 join projects as t2 on t2.unics_id=t1.project join institutions as t3 on t3.unics_id=t1.institution_id where t1.region_name='Dresden' and t2.framework_program='H2020' group by t3.institutions_name order by sum(t1.ec_contribution) desc, count(distinct t1.project) desc
